<br>
On a fluke one night I started a mage. I liked it immediately. Before long I started to love it. I soon realized that trying to split my play time between 3 chrs was slowing them all down (I work and go to college); so, I stripped the shammy, sold his equipment and placed him in the bazaar as a selling mule. <br>
<br>
It seems lately that I play my mage more than my cleric. The higher I go in level, the more fun I have. I have no doubt that my mage is becoming my main even though my cleric far out levels him. I may be getting a another computer soon (a really smokin laptop) and thought about setting up another account on it. <br>
<br>
When I realized my chances were very good for the getting the second computer, I started thinking about 2-boxing and what kind of chr I would use with my mage. I quickly dismissed the melee types because of reasons that have already been stated here. I have thought seriously about the other casters and healer types. <br>
<br>
I do not think I will pick a cleric or druid. Even though each has very strong points, I still think they have large limitations. <br>
I dismissed wizzies because they are aggro hogs. It might be difficult to get a mob off of a wizze if they aggro, even with a pet. Another mage would prolly work well, but I would prolly still spend a lot of time medding and letting my health bar go back up. I thought heavily about an enchanter. They have very big advantages, but in the end decided I wanted a chr that could melee in a pinch.<br>
<br>
I have always like the shaman as a playable chr. There happens to be a couple of really good ones in my guild. The more I think about it, the more I think that I agree with some of the previous posts. I think a mage / shammy combo would rock the world. The mages devastating ability to deal damage, coupled with the shammy's awesome ability to buff allies, debuff enemies, DoT and slow enemies, heal, and melee in a pinch make it the perfect match for a mage (imho).<br>
<br>
I hope to be able to test this theory out very soon.<br>
<br>
Anyway, just my 2 coppers worth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gallerus>Gallerus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 231<br> <font color=#333333>(2/12/03 8:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8754.topic&index=26>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2-boxin</span><hr size=1> &quot;Gnome cleric's have one of the lowest wisdom scores. Unless you are really set on playing a Gnome, I would choose another race. &quot;<br>
