BritLore ArchConvoker, TM <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=valherji>Valherji</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 247<br> <font color=#333333>(2/13/03 4:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=8754.topic&index=30>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Dual, boxing? Bah, try Quad boxing! Thats where the fun is at.... Mage, Enc, Cleric, Bard. rar.<br>
<br>
My choice for a second character though was a Bard, and wasn't created with 2 boxing in mind, but ended up working surprisingly well. Bards have a huge range of abilities that work great with Mages. <br>
<br>
Pre-pop, fear kiting ruled. My main AA source pre-pop was centis in ME, or in Akheva. Just me and my Bard could keep nearly the entire centi hill area clear by ourselves. Now with PoP levels and spells, I can go just about anywhere and tear everything apart. <br>
<br>
For bigger mobs, slow and bouncing in and out of melee is the trick. Bard would pull with slow, and send the pet on while singing mana and chants. Pet would start getting low, mage heals the pet and Bard goes in for melee w/ huge DS and regen twist. Bard gets low, back off and let pet take damage while regen'ing hp. Was able to kill a decent amount of things like this. FG full shroom packs + a bandit camp = good exp.<br>
<br>
And even in PoP era, Bard/Mage duo works nicely as there are a ton of wide-open zones (which Bards rule in). Fear is out, but aggro kiting is in. I was able to get an AA on each every 1.5 hours in HoHa in the temple basements. Bard pulls with slow, Mage malosinia's, Bard chant kites until 95%, send in pet. The Mage can nuke once for every 20% life, and have 1-2 extra nukes before he or the pet gains aggro. Im able to hold 8-9 spawns like this.<br>
<br>
Overall, you have to find out what works for you, as many classes compliment the Mage class nicely. Clerics are a great partner, and adding in a slower makes it a deadly trio. Enchanters are wonderful with their slow, kei, and charm (2 pets AND slow!). Shamans work very well with Mages also. You just need decide how you want your mob to die .<br>
<br>
-Valherji- <p>-Valherji-<br>
