<br>
What level are you &amp; the cleric ?<br>
<br>
The reason that cleric &gt; shaman for when you are less than level 60 is due to the fact that the cleric healing a pet generates 0 agro.  I used to fight anywhere between 3-5 mobs in chardok at a time using an aegoed epic pet &amp; let the mobs die to the pets dshield while the cleric ched the pet, pre-pop, this xp was just beyond wooty.  I would duo down fairly deep, setup shop &amp; just pull mobs non stop all night long.<br>
<br>
Post pop however, mage + cleric is simply not viable.  Without slow, you cannot hope to ever deal with even 1 add in a tier 1 zone even with a virtued pet that is getting chain ched.  Without slow vs 1 mob, a virtued pet requires just constant ching in tier 1 as it is.  Shaman + mage combo is far, far superior in pop than cleric + mage.  Post lvl 58 shaman can heal a pet virtually as well as a cleric &amp; they can mitigate a tremendous portion of damage via slow.<br>
<br>
The only instance I can think of where mage + cleric is a better duo is if you have lvl 65 charm &amp; limit yourself to like bot or other places where you can charm duo. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=412980">Lorcann</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
